node.text: Celebrate the last week of Hispanic Heritage Month with National Mixologist @janedangersays and the elevated flavors of the Batanga. This creative cocktail proves that the boldest flavors are never forgotten- and is easy enough to create at home 🍹 #TequilaElevated

node.text: Hispanic Heritage Month is starting on an elevated note as our National Mixologist @janedangersays celebrates the influence and flavors of the Chelada and the Michelada. With tips, history, and hacks you can easily mix along with Jane, or save for your next happy hour 🍹 #TequilaElevated

node.text:
Here’s to the bold spirits that keep us connected 🥃 
Tag the friend who’s always bringing people together for a good time and a great cocktail ⬇

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tequila Avion on July 13, 2021. May be an image of drink and text.

node.text: What does #TequilaElevated taste like? The finest single origin blue agave, slow roasted in brick ovens at a low temperature for 3 days 👀  Perfectly caramelized. Naturally rich flavors.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tequila Avion on June 20, 2021. May be an image of bottle.

node.text: You don’t have to be a father to appreciate the exceptional smoothness and complex taste of Reserva 44. But if you are, happy Father’s Day to you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tequila Avion on June 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, drink and outdoors.

node.text: It’s Thursday. Why not break out the reposado?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tequila Avion on June 12, 2021. May be an image of food and drink.

node.text: Reserva 44 Simple Serve. Perfection in a glass.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tequila Avion on June 10, 2021. May be an image of bottle.

node.text: That’s a good looking bottle of tequila.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tequila Avion on June 05, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, bottle and text.

node.text: Silver Saturdays are the best Saturdays.
